gomodel:SYNGO_168  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The authors use vGlut-pHluorin imaging and RNA knockdown to study the role of calcineurin A gamma (gene symbol PPP3CC) in the synaptic vesicle cycle. Knockdown led to a significant slowing of vesicle endocytosis. This was rescued by reintroduction of calcineurin gamma, but not alpha or beta isoforms. In addition, calcineurin gamma with a mutation in the catalytic domain of calcineurin also does not rescue. As control for the knockdown, immunofluoresence is provided.. Experimental description: Rat hippocampal neurons were co-transfected with a Ppp3cc-specific shRNA and the vGlut1-pHluorin construct, and immunocytochemistry analysis for\nCNA was performed to confirm knockdown of the CNA protein." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7620-2704" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1558-1958" ;
        dc:date           "2017-10-31" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_168" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .
